5 A BILL FOR AN ACT ENTITLED: “AN ACT REVISING THE COST FOR NONRESIDENT SMITH RIVER
6 BONUS POINTS; REVISING THE PORTION OF COMMERCIAL OUTFITTER CLIENT FEES DEPOSITED IN
7 THE SMITH RIVER CORRIDOR ENHANCEMENT ACCOUNT; AMENDING SECTION 23-2-409, MCA; AND
8 PROVIDING AN IMMEDIATE EFFECTIVE DATE.”
9
10 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF MONTANA:
11
12 Section 1. Section 23-2-409, MCA, is amended to read:
13 "23-2-409. Allocation of user fees -- expenditure of Smith River corridor enhancement account.
14 (1) All money collected as recreational and commercial user fees for floating and camping on the Smith River
15 waterway pursuant to 23-2-408 must be deposited in the state treasury in the Smith River corridor
16 enhancement account in the state special revenue fund to the credit of the department.
17 (2) (a) The following portions of recreational and commercial user fees deposited in the Smith
18 River corridor enhancement account must be used for the purposes in subsection (2)(b):
19 (i) $50 $75 of each commercial outfitter client fee;
20 (ii) all revenue from the sale of super permit lottery chances;
21 (iii) all revenue from sales of a resident-only $5 $10 bonus point and a nonresident $50 $125
22 bonus point; and
23 (iv) 5% of other float fee revenue, except for the nonrefundable permit application fee.
24 (b) The sum of the funds described in subsection (2)(a) must be expended to:
25 (i) protect and enhance the integrity of the natural and scenic beauty of the Smith River waterway
26 and its recreational, fisheries, and wildlife values through the lease or acquisition of property, including lease or
27 acquisition of partial interests in property by the department within the Smith River corridor;
